@page "/donate"

<section class="donate-hero">
    <h1>Support Ripple (Conceptual)</h1>
    <p>
        Ripple is a proof‑of‑concept project created for a college honors program. While the website 
        models how a community‑focused aquaponics nonprofit could operate, Ripple is not an active 
        organization and does not accept real donations. This page demonstrates how a donation 
        workflow might look in a fully implemented system.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Why Support Matters in This Model</h2>
    <p>
        In this academic project, Ripple is presented as a hypothetical year‑round aquaponics facility 
        designed to grow fresh leafy greens and tilapia for food‑insecure communities. Although the 
        system is not currently operating, the model explores how community support could enable:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Expanded food production for families in need</li>
        <li>Maintenance and scaling of aquaponic systems</li>
        <li>Educational workshops and community programming</li>
        <li>Research into sustainable and efficient food systems</li>
        <li>Development of replicable models for other communities</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Donation Process (Demonstration Only)</h2>
    <p>
        Ripple is described as a future <strong>501(c)(3)</strong> nonprofit organization for the 
        purposes of this honors project. This status is conceptual and not legally established. 
        No real donations are being collected, and the donation link below is a placeholder used 
        to illustrate how a secure giving portal would function in a real nonprofit setting.
    </p>

    <div class="donate-box">
        <a href="#" class="btn donate-btn">Make a Donation (Demo)</a>
        <p class="donate-note">
            (This is a placeholder link for demonstration only. No transactions will occur.)
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Other Ways to Support (Conceptually)</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Volunteering at a hypothetical facility</li>
        <li>Partnering with the project in a community‑based model</li>
        <li>Sharing the concept with others interested in sustainability</li>
        <li>Participating in educational events or workshops</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        These activities represent how community engagement could look if Ripple were implemented 
        as a real nonprofit initiative.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Thank You</h2>
    <p>
        Thank you for exploring Ripple and supporting the vision behind this honors project. 
        Your interest helps highlight the potential of sustainable, community‑driven food systems 
        in urban environments like Chicago.
    </p>
</section>
